<br>
    This makes SCM 1 2.5% savings, SCM 2 7.5% savings, and SCM 3 15% savings.  I hope this makes it clearer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1730<br> <font color=#333333>(8/6/02 2:23:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=296.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Improved reclaim</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If you chain pets or anything other then eat MS2 pets... then this skill isn't too bad.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I have not been bold enough to try reclaiming multiple pets through a single fight, it just seems too dangerous.  Since the new pet control buttons can be used during a spell cast <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (unlike the programmable hot keys)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I chained by tapping PET GO AWAY just before the cast of the next pet completes, and then PET ATTACK.<br>
